===Non-accessible areas===

The Great Pug also contains many rooms that are fully modelled, but not accessible in normal times, such as:

* The bottom floor under the stairs, unanimously called the "Basement", that is only opened on special occasions, containing some chairs, and leftover signage
* The kitchen
* A room next to the storage closet
* A tiny room behind the bar on the second floor

==Popularity==

As one of the oldest worlds in VRChat, The Great Pug is considered a ''classic'' world. Most people coming to this world are regulars, and as this world is not Quest Compatible, it can be for some a "refuge" world from the very popular instances of other worlds.

==Community==

The Great Pug is a meeting place for many content creators.
We've seen the first tests of "AI" players: players that use Large Language Models (think ChatGPT) to talk back to other players. 
Or players who have completely remastered the place by creating avatars that can add more content to the world (decorations, various objects...), making the place their own in a very creative way. 
Concerts are sometimes held on the second floor stage. 
It's also a meeting place for avatar creators. 

==Events==

The Great Pug celebrates two annual holidays, which began in 2017. During these seasonal events, a 'hunt' is promoted, where users will have to find several of an object scattered around The Great Pug.

===Saint Patrick's Day===

Since 2017. Users are encouraged to attend, and have their optimized avatar wear green.

===Halloween===

Since 2017. Users are encouraged to attend, and have their optimized avatars wear a spooky costume.

===Other events===

* Boogie in the Basement - 2023

==Easter eggs==

===The Hunt for Mr. Whiskers and The Dire Pug===

The '''Hunt for Mr. Whiskers''' was an event in April 2018 that sent players throughout various worlds in search of clues to find pieces to a gun that could ultimately destroy Mr. Whiskers. This event included the Great Pug, where resolving a puzzle unlocked a portal to a secret world called "Dire Pug".

The '''Dire Pug''' is a challenge world containing several trials to go through, the reward was a piece of the Mr. Whiskers gun.

In 2020, after the "Udon" update, the Dire Pug died and until this day puzzle and objects interactions have not been restored. (yet, who knows maybe it will reborn again)

===Robogenics Survey===

In 2022, A poster about '''"R Survey"''' was added, located next to the spawn where many posters are displayed. Players could pick up a USB stick object from this poster and use it to unlock a portal leading to the '''Robogenics survey''' world about the future of AIs in VRChat. (The pickup is now unavailable, [https://github.com/owlboy/greatpug-public/issues/186 pending reimplementation])

